  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "When there are multiple rook namespaces running, we observe that the flex volume drivers for the namespaces will conflict.\r\n- The agent pods will be watching the same unix socket \r\n- If one namespace is terminated, the unix socket will be deleted from under the agent in the other namespace\r\n\r\nThe latter is an issue commonly in the integration tests running in jenkins. Immediately after one test suite is removed, another suite starts. The removal might actually take several seconds to complete and will remove the socket from under the new namespace.\r\n\r\nTo allow multiple namespaces to use the flex driver, we will need to base the name of the flex driver on the namespace where the operator/agent pair are running. Since the drivers would be registered under rook.io, we wouldn't have to worry about conflicting with any other driver.\r\n",
